        "cooked": "<h1><a name=\"p-270918-proposal-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-270918-proposal-1\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Proposal</h1>\n<p>It should be possible for members in a group chat to flag/report messages of other members. Admins can get notified when a message is reported and check who reported it and why. Until a feature like <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/ability-for-group-admins-to-delete-any-message-for-everyone/22229/231\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Ability for group admins to delete any message for everyone - #231 by Bopva</a> is implemented, the admin canâ€™t do much beyond reprimand or kick the offending member.</p>\n<p><strong>Optional addition</strong></p>\n<p>Until an admin has reviewed a reported message, members have the option to hide the message they reported as well as hide messages reported by others. <em>This would <strong>only be visible on their own client</strong></em>.</p>\n<h1><a name=\"p-270918-background-2\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-270918-background-2\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Background</h1>\n<p>Currently, in order to make an admin or moderator aware of a potentially rule-breaking message, the user has two options: message the admin directly (with or without a screenshot) or <code>@</code> the admin in the group chat.</p>\n<p>This has two short-comings:<br>\nFirst, it breaks the flow of the chat. The discussion is interrupted by the call out.<br>\nSecond, in groups with multiple admins, every admin has to be addressed directly (related topic <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/groupmanagement-a-way-for-group-administrators-moderators-to-take-shifts/10241\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Groupmanagement: a way for group administrators/moderators to take shifts</a>)</p>\n<p>Reporting/flagging a message exists in many other chat software and could even be considered a tool in the belt of admins or moderators.</p>\n<h1><a name=\"p-270918-example-3\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-270918-example-3\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Example</h1>\n<p>A message is flagged by members of the group. When admins open the group chat, they see a flag icon and can scroll to flagged content.</p>\n<p>Until an admin has reviewed it other members could configure their signal client to take actions depending on preferred thresholds</p>\n<ul>\n<li>hide the message e.g say at least 50 people flagged a message â†’ itâ€™s hidden with a flag <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/triangular_flag_on_post.png?v=15\" title=\":triangular_flag_on_post:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":triangular_flag_on_post:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> and number of people who flagged it</li>\n<li>see a flag <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/triangular_flag_on_post.png?v=15\" title=\":triangular_flag_on_post:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":triangular_flag_on_post:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> e.g 10 people flagged a message â†’ <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/triangular_flag_on_post.png?v=15\" title=\":triangular_flag_on_post:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":triangular_flag_on_post:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> is shown on post</li>\n<li>do nothing regardless of the number of flags</li>\n</ul>",
